# Portfolio Code Conventions

## Structure
- App Router: `src/app/` (layout, page, globals.css, `api/chat/`)
- Sections: `src/components/sections/` — one component per scroll section
- Chat UI: `src/components/chat/`
- Shared UI: `src/components/`
- Static content: `src/utils/data.ts` (typed exports, `satisfies`)
- Chat knowledge: `docs/` → `src/lib/knowledge/` (index, retrieval, prompts)
- GSAP client import: `@/lib/gsap-client` (not raw `gsap` in components)

## Components
- Sections with GSAP or hooks: `"use client"` at top
- Footer without interactivity: server component OK
- Language: `useLanguage()` from `@/context/TextContext`
- Localized strings: `Record<Language, T>` or `LocalizedText` from `data.ts`

## Styling
- Tailwind only — match existing palette (sky/slate)
- Responsive: mobile-first, `md:` / `lg:` breakpoints like existing sections
- Keep animation subtle; respect reduced motion patterns if adding new motion

## Data changes
- Static UI copy: add to `data.ts` first, then wire component
- Chat facts: edit `docs/*.md`, run `npm run index-knowledge`
- New navbar item: update `hero[language].navbar` + section `id`
- Project detail anchor: `refMore: "#slug"` matches `id={detail.logo}` in Details

## Chat / knowledge
- Stream path: `api/chat/route.ts` → `rag-chat-stream.ts`
- Tests live alongside libs (`*.test.ts`); run `npm run test` after logic changes
- Env: `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`; optional Redis/Upstash for chat-store on Vercel

## Don't
- Move static content into components as hardcoded strings — keep `data.ts` as single source
- Invent portfolio facts in code or prompts without user confirmation
- Large refactors when user asked for a small focused change
